Perfect! I can now see the issue clearly. The bug is on lines 475-482:

```go
if isRecentlyActive {
    // Session is recently active - check if it's actually processing
    // This is the expensive check, but we only do it for recently active sessions
    if client.IsSessionProcessing(session.ID) {
        skippedActive++
        continue
    }
}
untrackedSessions = append(untrackedSessions, session)
```

The problem is that `IsSessionProcessing()` is only called for sessions that are "recently active" (updated within the last 5 minutes). Sessions that are idle for more than 5 minutes but are still actively being used (e.g., someone is reading the output or thinking) will bypass this check entirely and get added to the `untrackedSessions` list to be deleted.

The fix is straightforward: call `IsSessionProcessing()` for ALL untracked sessions, not just recently active ones. The only difference is that recently active sessions will continue to be skipped without deletion, but ALL sessions should be checked for active processing before being considered for deletion.

