Current logic (lines 469-485):
```go
for _, session := range diskSessions {
    if !trackedSessionIDs[session.ID] {
        // Quick check: was this session recently active?
        updatedAt := time.Unix(session.Time.Updated/1000, 0)
        isRecentlyActive := now.Sub(updatedAt) <= recentActivityThreshold

        if isRecentlyActive {
            // Only check IsSessionProcessing() for recently active sessions
            if client.IsSessionProcessing(session.ID) {
                skippedActive++
                continue
            }
        }
        untrackedSessions = append(untrackedSessions, session)
    }
}
```

The bug: Sessions that are NOT recently active (idle >5min) bypass the `IsSessionProcessing()` check and get added to `untrackedSessions` for deletion.

The fix: Call `IsSessionProcessing()` for ALL untracked sessions:
```go
for _, session := range diskSessions {
    if !trackedSessionIDs[session.ID] {
        // Check if session is currently processing
        if client.IsSessionProcessing(session.ID) {
            skippedActive++
            continue
        }
        untrackedSessions = append(untrackedSessions, session)
    }
}
```

This removes the 5-minute recency threshold entirely. The cost is one API call per untracked session, but this is acceptable because it prevents active sessions from being deleted.

